io.orchestrate.client.dao

Interface AsyncDao<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type this object will control CRUD operations for.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GenericAsyncDao

    public interface AsyncDao<T>
    Interface for generic Create, Read, Update, and Delete (CRUD) operations on a collection for the specified type.

      • save

        java.util.concurrent.Future<KvMetadata> save(java.lang.String key,
                                           T value,
                                           boolean ifAbsent)
        Save the specified value to the key if and only if the key does not already exist when ifAbsent is true.

        If ifAbsent is true and the key already exists the result of the Future will be null.

        Parameters:
        key - The key to save the specified value to.
        value - The object to save.
        ifAbsent - When true the store operation will only succeed if the specified key does not already exist.
        Returns:
        A future for the metadata about the saved object.
